  "guided": true,
  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "A good essay flows when the typing stops getting in the way of the thinking. Loop each word until it runs itself, then let your ideas pour out clean. Flow, not force."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Hands on home row, eyes off the keys. Repeat each word at one even pace - same gap between every tap. Don't push the pace, let the steady beat set it for you."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "🎶",
      "title": "Even beat",
      "text": "Lock a tempo you can hold the whole way. Smooth and even beats fast and jerky every time - steady hands keep the sentence flowing. Trust the rhythm and ride it."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "change change change change change",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Rhythm: change",
      "hint": "Loop it on the beat: change - change - change. Same gap every time."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "courage courage courage courage",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Rhythm: courage",
      "hint": "Hold the tempo: courage - courage - courage. Flow, not force."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "future future future future",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: future",
      "hint": "Stay even to the end: future - future - future. Don't rush the finish."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Feel the longer words landing as one smooth move? That is what carries an essay - even reps turn effort into reflex, so the words keep pace with the ideas instead of dragging behind."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "All three drills done? Hit \"Open trainer\" below and run the full lesson text in one go. That run saves to your progress and unlocks the next lesson."
    }
